overview: The user initiated a review of a sleep questionnaire application to
  verify its adherence to the project's Statement of Work and detailed
  specifications. The assistant performed a comprehensive analysis, outlining
  both successfully implemented features and significant gaps, such as the
  absence of a tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, and outbound links in
  the report. Following this review, the assistant began implementing the
  identified high-priority tasks. The first task, currently in progress,
  involves integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference,
  complete with critical safety warnings for high scores. This required updates
  to the application's data types, validation schema, and the user interface for
  the daytime sleepiness section.
